Convert-Color-IRC

This module is a set of funtions that allows one to
take a traditional IRC color number and return either
its hex code or name.  Note that this module assumes
the default color choices for IRC programs.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Convert::Color::IRC

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Convert-Color-IRC

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Convert-Color-IRC

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Convert-Color-IRC

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Convert-Color-IRC/


